http://yourstru.ly/ Shortly after meeting John Vanderslice and Minna Choi in the lobby of the SF Conservatory of Music, a good-natured debate about the NBA playoffs became the best ice breaker in awkward history. The fact is, JV and Minna make a great team; the level of mutual respect bouncing back and forth between the two of them is like watching Stockton and Malone mid pick and roll. item.title: Skate 2 Arcade Style 2 (& Bloopers) (machinima)
item.description:
Skate 2 Arcade Style 2 (& Bloopers) (machinima)
SKATE 2 Machinima.com director BenBuja presents the secondskate 2 arcade style video. If you see this video choppy/laggy in HD, try putting the playback slider to the beginning of the video. "We tried to make the tricks as over-the-top as possible and focused mainly on wallrides, bodyflips and huge gaps, but there are also some hippieflips to grinds and other tricks. The bloopers part begins at 3:25, feel free to skip to that if you really can't stand unrealistic tricks in this videogame. We were pretty surprised about the mostly positive feedback of our first arcade style video so we decided to make another one thats even more extreme. And no, we won't go play Tony Hawk, its more fun and challenging to do this in skate lol." BenBujas Youtube page: http://www.youtube.com/user/BenBuja FOR MORE MACHINIMA GOTO: http://www.youtube.com/subscription_center?add_user=machinima
